    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The CIFAR-10 dataset is one of the most classic image recognition datasets.\n",
        "It consists of 60,000 tiny color images (32×32 pixels) divided into 10 classes:\n",
        "\n",
        "Label\tClass\n",
        "\n",
        "0\tairplane\n",
        "\n",
        "1\tautomobile\n",
        "\n",
        "2\tbird\n",
        "\n",
        "3\tcat\n",
        "\n",
        "4\tdeer\n",
        "\n",
        "5\tdog\n",
        "\n",
        "6\tfrog\n",
        "\n",
        "7\thorse\n",
        "\n",
        "8\tship\n",
        "\n",
        "9\ttruck\n",
        "\n",
        "Each image is a small RGB picture.\n",
        "Even though this dataset is simple by modern standards, it’s perfect for learning the basics of image classification."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3XHZeUdUCWM9"
      }
    },
