      "source": [
        "### Define the Neural Network\n",
        "\n",
        "* Input layer: 32×32×3 = 3072 features\n",
        "\n",
        "* Hidden layers: 3 layers with Tanh activation\n",
        "\n",
        "* Output layer: 2 neurons for airplane/bird (no softmax needed; handled by CrossEntropyLoss)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "R5pV9P4MJTTI"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "model = nn.Sequential(\n",
        "    nn.Linear(32*32*3, 1024),  # Flattened input\n",
        "    nn.Tanh(),\n",
        "    nn.Linear(1024, 512),\n",
        "    nn.Tanh(),\n",
        "    nn.Linear(512, 128),\n",
        "    nn.Tanh(),\n",
        "    nn.Linear(128, 2)          # 2 output logits for binary classification\n",
        ")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "T8KgCdIiJQSX"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Define Loss and Optimizer\n",
        "\n",
        "CrossEntropyLoss combines LogSoftmax + NLLLoss, so we don’t apply softmax in the network."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kheN2Io6JqI8"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "loss_fn = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()         # For multi-class (binary) classification\n",
        "optimizer = optim.SGD(model.parameters(), lr=1e-2)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "blS5J3CQJdoU"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Training Loop\n",
        "\n",
